<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1394">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/137.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Action reported in your No. 281 approved. The contract has been referred
                            to the War Department for study and report. Would it, in your judgment,
                            be advisable to have a commission examine this contract as was done in
                            the case of the Agua Dulce Railway?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>